{"title":"Randomized parameters","markdown":{"headingText":"Randomized parameters","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"::: {.question}\n\n**Aurora Technologies — Adjusting WACC for Corporate Taxes**\n\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| results: asis\n#| echo: false\n#| warning: false\n\nset.seed(707)\nlibrary(webexercises)\nlibrary(knitr)\n\npre_tax_wacc <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 14, sd = 0.2), 2) / 100\ncorporate_tax_rate <- 0.25\npre_tax_cost_of_debt <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 7, sd = 0.2), 2) / 100\ndebt_to_value <- 0.55\n\n# After-tax WACC adjustment\nafter_tax_wacc <- pre_tax_wacc - (debt_to_value * corporate_tax_rate * pre_tax_cost_of_debt)\n```\n\nSolar Technologies currently has a pre-tax WACC of `r round(pre_tax_wacc*100, 1)`%. The corporate tax rate is `r corporate_tax_rate*100`%, and the pre-tax cost of debt is `r round(pre_tax_cost_of_debt*100,1)`%. If the company issues enough debt to reach a debt-to-value ratio of `r debt_to_value`, compute the after-tax WACC (in %). \n\n\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;\"> <label for=\"module7_num_q2a_single\"><strong>After-tax WACC (%):</strong></label> <input type=\"number\" id=\"module7_num_q2a_single\" name=\"module7_num_q2a_single\" style=\"width:160px;\" data-correct-answer=`r round(after_tax_wacc*100, 2)` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" step=\"0.01\" /> </form> <div id=\"feedback-module7_num_q2a_single\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\"> ✅ $WACC_{after} = w_E r_E + w_D r_D(1 - T_c)= w_E r_E + w_D r_D - w_D r_D T_c$<br>\n  Since $WACC_{pre} = w_E r_E + w_D r_D = 13.7\\%$, then<br>\n  $WACC_{after} = 13.7\\% - (0.55 \\times 6.9\\% \\times 0.25) = \\mathbf{12.75\\%}.$ </div>\n\n:::\n\n:::\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false